description: A bit-mask indicating which ifIndices (ports) are members of this hunting group.
Multiple POTS ports providing emergency service and distributed over various line
cards can be assigned to a hunting group. The same ports can be assigned to various
hunting groups at the same time.
The bit-mask is in the form of an Octet String of size 256 octets (2048 bits).
Each bit represents a value of an ifIndex in the range 0..2047 beginning from
bit 0 in Octet 1 (ifIndex=0) to bit 7 in Octet 256 (ifIndex=2047).
The octet for a given ifIndex is given by use of integer division as follows:
(ifIndex\8)+1
The bit number within the octet calculated above is then given by
ifIndex MOD 8
E.g., for ifIndex = 101:
bit = ifIndex MOD 8 = 5
A set bit indicates that the associated port is a member of this hunting group.

description: Indicates that SN attribute on whole MSAN level is modified.
In case of Local call support (enabled for at least one VGW), SN attribute has to be configured on whole MSAN level:
SN Attribute = Unique: multiple local areas not supported. All the subscriber numbers are unique in whole MSAN scope. (DN=SN)
SN Attribute = Multiple: multiple local areas are supported. Subscriber numbers are unique in own local area but could be ambiguous across local areas. (DN=LAC+SN)
